-- Copper in London Slumps to $6,795 Per Metric Ton, First Drop in Four Days
-- Glenys Sim
-- 2010-07-22T00:02:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-22/copper-in-london-slumps-to-6-795-per-metric-ton-first-drop-in-four-days.html

          
          
             Copper declined for the first time
in four days, by as much as 1 percent, to $6,795 a metric ton.
The contract for three-month delivery on the London Metal
Exchange traded 0.8 percent lower at $6,805 a ton by 8:02 a.m.
in Singapore.  
          
          


  


        